  "body": "**Kubernetes version** (use `kubectl version`):\r\nv1.4.6\r\n\r\n**Environment**:\r\n- **Cloud provider or hardware configuration**: AWS\r\n- **OS** (e.g. from /etc/os-release): CoreOS v1235.2.0\r\n- **Kernel** (e.g. `uname -a`):\r\n4.8.6-coreos-r1 #1 SMP Wed Dec 7 00:29:42 UTC 2016 x86_64 Intel(R) Xeon(R) CPU E5-2676 v3 @ 2.40GHz GenuineIntel GNU/Linux\r\n\r\n**What happened**:\r\nWhen creating a service-type loadBalancer, adding `service.beta.kubernetes.io/aws-load-balancer-internal` creates an internal ELB, but the only allowed value for `loadBalancerSourceRanges` is 0.0.0.0/0. This limitation prevents you from specifying custom CIDR range for your hybrid cloud (Direct Connect to private data center)\r\n\r\n**What you expected to happen**:\r\nThe limitation is unnecessary. Even in an AWS only scenario (no hybrid cloud), it makes sense to allow a CIDR range for a subnet where your calling services are deployed.\r\n\r\n**How to reproduce it** (as minimally and precisely as possible):\r\nCreate a service-type loadBalancer and set loadBalancerSourceRanges to a value other than 0.0.0.0/0\r\n",
